body:
**How a Death Should feel:**
&quot;Well damn, I made a bad play (or they made a good play,etc.) resulting in my death. Well, Now that they have some gold and time to farm, position, or push lane, I should play a bit more careful, maybe we could, as a team, stop this from going anywhere or even take advantage of their killing me by taking other points.&quot;

**How a death feels right now:**
&quot;Welp, I died, they now have gold, farm, dragon, a turret so _all _ of their team has gold, they have the option to freeze lane, can complete another item, can roam to kill another lane, basically our chances of winning has diminished severely, and I have 5 seconds left to respawn...&quot;

What do you think? Now, I know that there are a LOT of other factors resulting in this (Terrible turrets, snowball-y games, etc.) But I am just getting annoyed by the death timers. Deaths should be punishing, but not game defining by 15 minutes in game.
